            <img src="imagessouth/maincourse/Masala Dosa.jpg" alt="dosa">
            <div class="card-content">
                <h3>Masala Dosa</h3>
                <p>Masala Dosa is a popular South Indian crepe made from a fermented batter of rice and lentils (mainly urad dal). The batter is spread thinly on a hot griddle, creating a large, crispy dosa. A flavorful potato filling, typically made with boiled and mashed potatoes tempered with mustard seeds, curry leaves, onions, and spices, is spread inside the dosa. Masala Dosa is often served with coconut chutney and sambar.
</p>
                <p>Price: &#8377;1000</p>
                <span style="background-color: #28a745; color: white; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">Veg</span>  
            </div>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div class="card">
            <img src="imagessouth/maincourse/Uttapam.jpg" alt="uttapam">
            <div class="card-content">
                <h3>Uttapam</h3>
                <p> Uttapam is a savory South Indian pancake made from a batter of fermented rice and lentils, similar to dosa batter. However, uttapam is thicker and fluffier than dosa. It's cooked on a hot griddle with various toppings such as finely chopped onions, tomatoes, green chilies, cilantro, and sometimes grated carrots or cheese. Uttapam is typically served with coconut chutney and sambar.
</p>
                <p>Price: &#8377;600</p>
                <span style="background-color: #28a745; color: white; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">Veg</span>  
            </div>
        </div>
