                <p>The Varan is made from pigeon peas (toor dal) cooked with turmeric, salt, and sometimes a tadka (tempering) of ghee, mustard seeds, cumin seeds, curry leaves, and green chilies. It is usually a smooth and mildly spiced lentil curry, providing a balance of flavors and textures to the meal.</p>
